title: Grateful Dead Live at Nassau Coliseum on 1981-05-08
lineage: NAK-700's > SONY TC-D5M  Dolby On, FOB
description: Jack Straw, Peggy-O, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Loser, CC Rider-> Althea, Let It Grow-> Don't Ease Me In Shakedown Street-> Samson & Delilah, Terrapin Station-> Playin' In The Band-> Drums*-> Nobody's Fault But Mine-> Not Fade Away-> Stella Blue-> Sugar Magnolia, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: Friday Night at Nassau This was one of the greatest Dead shows I ever saw.  An inspired show all the way through.  Stella Blue is the best version I have ever heard.  Ken Kesey plays harmonica with the Rhythm Devils.  Six out of Five stars... quite possibly the best Dead show I ever saw
gets 5 nasty little gem that needs to be rec'd more often.
awesome! this is the first show i got from this site. anyone got any other suggestions...this show is badass!!!!

Suggestions for timlistenstodead My suggestion would be to look through the Dead collection for any and all shows that are downloadable and get them all!! Unless, of course, they have poor ratings, but I've found that the majority are great...including this one!!
good suggestion! i have been downloading as previously been suggested, great minds me thinks!

Good show but... I downloaded this show a year or two ago, one thing I would like to point out is the phil bombs get insane during the second set so watch out if you care about your speakers.

Awesome show which is on fire with energy.  Jerry is taking command during this show.
Shakedown St. Just gotta poke around on Shakedown Street. You'll find what you need.

1st cut is the deepest This was one of my 1st shows, it was all new to me and most of it blew me away.  I still have a deep fondness in my heart for Peggy-O and would argue that Jack Straw is as fine an opener as there ever was, but going back and listening to this show the let it grow stands out the most to me.  I was 17 my friends were into punk and gave me a lot of $hit about the dead, but I would challenge anyone to stand in front of that band hear these songs and not become a fan?
